Done in ece50d3. Removed `SKGestureSurfaceView` from the library. The sample now demonstrates using `SKGestureTracker` directly with a standard `SKCanvasView`:

```csharp
// Create tracker
private readonly SKGestureTracker _tracker = new();

// Wire up touch
private void OnTouch(object? sender, SKTouchEventArgs e)
{
    e.Handled = _tracker.ProcessTouch(e);
    if (e.Handled) canvasView.InvalidateSurface();
}

// Subscribe to needed events
_tracker.TapDetected += OnTap;
_tracker.PanDetected += OnPan;
```

Kept `SKGestureTrackerExtensions.cs` for the convenient `ProcessTouch()` method.
